{{Quote|Supreme Chancellor, delegates of the Senate; A tragedy has occurred which started right here with the taxation of trade routes, and has now engulfed our entire planet in the oppression of the Trade Federation.|Palpatine's address to the Senate during the Invasion of Naboo|<ref name="The Phantom Menace" />}}
'''Senate Resolution BR-0371''' was passed by the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic Senate]] in [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]] after the failed [[Eriadu Trade Summit]]. It created taxation for [[Hyperspace route/Legends|hyperspace routes]] [[Free Trade Zone/Legends|in the]] [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer]] and [[Mid Rim/Legends|Mid Rims]], with the profit going to pay off the growing budget crisis in the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]. [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] of [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]], who was secretly the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] Sidious, was a prominent supporter of the resolution.

Darth Sidious used BR-0371 to convince the [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation]] to [[Invasion of Naboo/Legends|blockade]] [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]]. The plan to get rid of it was to have [[Queen/Legends|Queen]] [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Padmé Amidala]] sign a "treaty" making Naboo a Federation protectorate to legitimize their occupation, which would be sent to the Senate. Instead, the Queen [[Battle of Naboo/Legends#Retaking the Palace|turned the tables]] and forced the Viceroy to sign another treaty.

==Description==
A seemingly innocuous bill,<ref name="Galactic Battlegrounds" /> [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Senate]] Resolution BR-0371 created a [[Currency/Legends|tariff]] on [[Hyperspace route/Legends|hyperlane]] trade routes from the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]] to the [[Mid Rim/Legends|Mid Rim]]. It was introduced to pay off the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic's]] growing fiscal debt,<ref name="The Essential Chronology">[[The Essential Chronology (real-world book)|''The Essential Chronology'']]</ref> and used to support relief and development projects in outlying [[Star system/Legends|systems]].<ref name="Galactic Battlegrounds" />

==History==
===Background and passage===
{{Quote|It seems almost absurd that the momentous shift from Republic to Empire grew out of something as trivial as a taxation dispute, but the most injurious evil is rarely accompanied by tremors and thunderclaps.|The New Republic [[Historical Council]] in 25 ABY|<ref name="The Essential Chronology" />}}
The Galactic Republic had been in a period of decline and political corruption, with [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Finis Valorum/Legends|Finis Valorum]] embroiled in a corruption scandal.<ref name="The Essential Chronology" /> [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] of [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]], secretly the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] Sidious,<ref name="DP">[[Darth Plagueis (novel)|''Darth Plagueis'']]</ref> urged Valorum to limit the power of the [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation]], a galactic conglomerate that functionally controlled every trade route in the Republic.<ref name="Galactic Battlegrounds" /> Palpatine supported Senate Resolution BR-0371<ref name="The Essential Chronology" /> as part of the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] [[Grand Plan/Legends|Grand Plan]], hoping to bring the declining Republic into further turmoil to reinstate Sith rule of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]].<ref name="DP" />

===Reactions===
[[File:TF_Battleship.png|thumb|right|300px|The Blockade of Naboo was caused by the Trade Federation in reaction to BR-0371.]]
Senate Resolution BR-0371 was a resounding success for the Republic, acquiring the intended development funds. Within a month of its passage, the Trade Federation suffered significant financial losses as a result of BR-0371, losing profits through the taxation of the previously [[Free Trade Zone/Legends|Free Trade Zone]] they controlled. The Federation senator [[Lott Dod/Legends|Lott Dod]] argued against taxation in the Senate while the Trade Federation Directorate began planning their counterstrike. [[Viceroy of the Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation Viceroy]] [[Nute Gunray/Legends|Nute Gunray]] and [[Rune Haako/Legends|Rune Haako]] supervised the secret expansion of their [[Trade Federation Droid Army/Legends|Droid Army]].<ref name="Galactic Battlegrounds" /> Through the manipulations of Palpatine in the guise of Darth Sidious,<ref name="DP" /> six [[Standard month/Legends|months]] after the passage of BR-0371, the Trade Federation launched a blockade of Palpatine's [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]]. The blockade involved a fleet of battleships placed in orbit around the planet, preventing trade through Naboo and causing its [[Naboo (people)/Legends|inhabitants]] to become desperate. After the Senate still refused to overturn Senate Resolution BR-0371, the Federation launched a full scale [[Invasion of Naboo/Legends|Invasion of Naboo]].<ref name="Galactic Battlegrounds" />

Naboo's [[Monarch of Naboo/Legends|Queen]] [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Padmé Amidala]] was [[Capture of Theed/Legends|rescued]] from the Federation's clutches by [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] and taken to the galactic [[Capital/Legends|capital]] [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. The queen presented her planet's crisis to the Senate, but when Valorum was unable to act due to the corruption and bureaucracy of the Senate, she called a [[Vote of No Confidence/Legends|Vote of No Confidence]] on the chancellor, on Palpatine's advice.<ref name="The Phantom Menace" /> The unpopular Valourum was voted out, and as Palpatine had planned, he receieved the nomination for chancellor and [[Supreme Chancellor election, 32 BBY/Legends|won]] due to the sympathy generated for the senator's besieged homeworld. Naboo was later [[Battle of Naboo/Legends|freed]] by an alliance led by Amidala, and Palpatine became the last Supreme Chancellor,<ref name="The Essential Chronology" /> exceeding his term limits and [[Declaration of a New Order|transforming]] the Republic into the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]<ref name="Revenge of the Sith">{{Film|III}}</ref> in [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]].<ref name="The New Essential Chronology">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> Decades later, the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] rose from the fall of the Empire, and a [[Historical Council]] published Palpatine's full motivation of the resolution in an historical document, where they noted the absurdity that the galactic government had been changed as a result of a taxation dispute.<ref name="The Essential Chronology" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|Turmoil has engulfed the Galactic Republic. The taxation of trade routes to outlying star systems is in dispute. Hoping to resolve the matter with a blockade of deadly battleships, the greedy Trade Federation has stopped all shipping to the small planet of Naboo.|The opening crawl of ''Star Wars: Episode I - The Phantom Menace''|<ref name="The Phantom Menace" />}}
The taxation of trade routes was alluded to in the [[1999]] [[prequel trilogy]] [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']], written and directed by [[George Lucas]].<ref name="The Phantom Menace" /> It was identified as Senate Resolution BR-0371 in the [[2000]] reference book [[The Essential Chronology (real-world book)|''The Essential Chronology'']].<ref name="The Essential Chronology" />

